WEBVTT

00:07.357 --> 00:10.292
This is for your father.
Loaded with antioxidants

00:10.326 --> 00:11.623
and good for his heart muscle.

00:11.661 --> 00:14.697
Ignacio Suarez drinking
pomegranate juice.

00:14.697 --> 00:18.657
He used to hate this stuff.
Elena, you are a miracle worker.

00:18.702 --> 00:21.000
Just doing my job. Try it.

00:24.208 --> 00:26.005
- Mmm...
- Mmm.

00:28.012 --> 00:29.877
Pomegranate juice was my idea,
you know.

00:29.913 --> 00:31.245
Oh, here we go.

00:31.283 --> 00:34.514
Way before it was in the stores.
Way before.

00:34.586 --> 00:37.714
And now some lady who stole my idea
is living in a mansion in Beverly Hills.

00:37.789 --> 00:39.051
I should be in Beverly Hills.

00:39.090 --> 00:41.058
No, I should be living in Beverly Hills.

00:41.092 --> 00:43.356
You don't want to live
in Beverly Hills, okay?

00:43.395 --> 00:45.193
I worked there for a year.

00:45.231 --> 00:49.099
Bunch of stuck-up old hags with
pulled-up faces. And their wives.

00:50.202 --> 00:52.670
<i>Good morning, familia!</i>

00:52.705 --> 00:57.074
It's a beautiful 30-degree day
in Queens, New York.

00:57.109 --> 01:00.978
Perfect weather for a brisky,
blood-pumping walk.

01:01.014 --> 01:02.948
I don't think "brisky" is a word.

01:02.983 --> 01:04.177
It is today.

01:04.217 --> 01:07.084
Ignacio, you gotta drink your juice
before your walk.

01:07.154 --> 01:10.555
Crazy idea. We can drink
and walk at the same time.

01:11.792 --> 01:15.125
- Have a nice walk!
- Yeah, have fun!

01:15.897 --> 01:18.832
Wow, I am so happy!

01:18.866 --> 01:22.393
<i>I can't believe how quickly papi has
bounced back from his heart attack.</i>

01:22.437 --> 01:24.928
I know. And how great is Elena?

01:24.972 --> 01:29.932
She's like the big sister I never had.
Now I know how important I am to you.

01:29.977 --> 01:31.878
Hmm. Well, she is amazing.

01:32.981 --> 01:34.608
And it's just
so nice not to have to worry.

01:34.650 --> 01:36.311
I know. I'll see you later.

01:36.352 --> 01:37.376
Mrs. Meade?

01:37.419 --> 01:38.750
Good morning, Betty.

01:38.787 --> 01:41.984
I tried to reach Daniel.
I'm in a bit of a pickle.

01:42.057 --> 01:46.586
Could you come to the drugstore
at 58th and Lex? And bring some cash.

01:47.664 --> 01:49.791
There's been a misunderstanding.

01:51.501 --> 01:56.803
I apprehended the suspect
leaving the store with this in her purse.

01:58.074 --> 02:02.603
Okay. Well, first of all, you don't have to
call her a suspect. It's Claire Meade.

02:02.646 --> 02:05.672
I don't care who she is.
Woman got the sticky fingers.

02:05.716 --> 02:08.116
Mrs. Meade,
did you shoplift?

02:08.151 --> 02:11.588
